ed%20by%20the%20earlier%20AIADMK%20government.%20A%20furious%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Assembly%20then%20held%20a%20special%20session%20on%20Saturday%20to%20re-adopt%20all%20ten%20bills%2C%20which%20were%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20Governor%20for%20his%20assent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftamil-nadu-governor-returns-10-bills-week-after-court-expressed-concerns-4578952%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%20Governor%20Returns%2010%20Bills%2C%20Week%20After%20Court%20Expressed%20Concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20this%20morning%20noted%20this%20development%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAssembly%20has%20passed%20the%20bills%20again%20and%20sent%20it%20to%20the%20Governor.%20Let%20us%20see%20what%20Governor%20does%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20adjourned%20the%20matter%20till%20December%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20bills%20are%20re-passed%2C%20they%20are%20on%20the%20same%20footing%20as%20money%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Ftamil-nadu%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%20government%20has%20accused%20the%20BJP-appointed%20Governor%20of%20deliberately%20delaying%20the%20bills'%20clearance%20and%20scuttling%20the%20state's%20development%20by%20%26quot%3Bundermining%20the%20elected%20administration%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20approach%20to%20the%20court%2C%20the%20ruling%20DMK%20said%20the%20Governor's%20actions%20were%20%26quot%3Bundermining%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%26quot%3B%20by%20deliberately%20delaying%20bills%20sent%20for%20clearance%20and%20asked%20for%20a%20specific%20timeframe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20pending%20bills%20is%20one%20that%20clips%20the%20Governor's%20authority%20to%20appoint%20Vice%20Chancellors%20of%20state-run%20universities%2C%20and%20another%20seeking%20prosecution%20of%20ex-ministers%20from%20the%20AIADMK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20today's%20hearing%2C%20there%20was%20a%20back-and-forth%20between%20senior%20advocates%20Abhishek%20Singhvi%20and%20Mukul%20Rohatgi%20(representing%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government)%20and%20the%20Solicitor-General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20(arguing%20for%20Mr%20Ravi).%20%26quot%3BThe%20Governor%20returned%20the%20bills%20stating%20'I%20withhold%20assent'%20without%20giving%20any%20reason...%20The%20Governor%20has%20violated%20every%20word%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20two%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20the%20Solicitor-General%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Governor%20is%20not%20a%20mere%20technical%20supervisor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20Mr%20Ravi%20had%20assented%20to%20162%20of%20181%20bills%20presented%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20noted%20the%20Governor%20of%20any%20state%2C%20under%20Article%20200%2C%20has%20three%20options%20-%20assent%20to%20bills%20presented%20to%20him%2C%20withhold%20that%20assent%2C%20or%20send%20it%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20proviso%20says%20Governor%20may%20send%20it%20to%20state%20government%20for%20reconsideration%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-on-punjab-vs-governor-over-bills-need-soul-searching-on-both-sides-4552546%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGovernors%20Must%20Remember%20They%20Aren't%20Elected%20Representatives%3A%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCan%20the%20Governor%20withhold%20assent%20on%20a%20bill%20without%20sending%20it%20back%20to%20the%20Assembly%3F%26quot%3B%20it%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Ravi%20had%20earlier%20also%20returned%20the%20NEET%20Exemption%20Bill%2C%20after%20much%20delay%2C%20and%20forwarded%20it%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India%20