www.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Foberoi-realty-enters-delhi-ncr-buys-15-acre-land-in-gurugram-for-rs-597-cr-123112000151_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Sam%20Altman's%20Shock%20Ouster%20From%20OpenAI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHealthy%20companies%20led%20by%20competent%2C%20commercially%20successful%20and%20globally%20beloved%20founders%20generally%20don't%20tend%20to%20fire%20them.%20And%2C%20as%20Sam%20Altman%20walked%20on%20stage%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20Nov.%206%2C%20all%20those%20things%20could%20have%20described%20his%20role%20at%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-founder%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20had%20kicked%20off%20a%20global%20race%20for%20artificial%20intelligence%20supremacy%2C%20helped%20OpenAI%20surpass%20much%20larger%20competitors%2C%20and%20was%2C%20by%20this%20point%2C%20regularly%20compared%20to%20Bill%20Gates%20and%20Steve%20Jobs.%20Eleven%20days%20later%20he%20would%20be%20fired%20-%20replaced%20by%20chief%20technology%20officer%20Mira%20Murati%2C%20kicking%20off%20a%20chaotic%20weekend%20during%20which%20executives%20loyal%20to%20Altman%20were%20agitating%20for%20his%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20on%20Nov.%206%2C%20at%20the%20company's%20first%20developer%20conference%2C%20the%20acclaim%20for%20Altman%20seemed%20universal.%20Attendees%20applauded%20rapturously%20as%20he%20ticked%20off%20the%20company's%20accomplishments%3A%202%20million%20customers%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bover%2092%25%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20big%20reason%20for%20that%20was%20Microsoft%20Corp.%2C%20which%20invested%20%2413%20billion%20into%20the%20company%20and%20put%20Altman%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20corporate%20overhaul%20that%20has%20caused%20it%20to%20leapfrog%20rivals%20like%20Google%20and%20Amazon%20in%20certain%20categories%20of%20cloud%20computing%2C%20reinvigorated%20its%20Bing%20search%20engine%2C%20and%20put%20the%20company%20in%20the%20leading%20position%20in%20the%20hottest%20software%20category.%20Now%2C%20Altman%20invited%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20onto%20the%20stage%20and%20asked%20him%20how%20Microsoft%20felt%20about%20the%20partnership.%20Nadella%20started%20to%20respond%2C%20and%20then%20broke%20into%20laughter%2C%20as%20if%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20question%20was%20absurdly%20obvious.%20%26quot%3BWe%20love%20you%20guys%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20finally%20said%20after%20he'd%20calmed%20down.%20He%20thanked%20Altman%20for%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20something%20magical.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20customers%20and%20investors%20were%20happy%2C%20there%20was%20one%20constituency%20that%20remained%20deeply%20skeptical%20of%20Altman%20and%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20a%20commercial%20AI%20company%3A%20Altman's%20own%20board%20of%20directors.%20Although%20the%20board%20included%20Altman%20and%20a%20close%20ally%2C%20OpenAI%20President%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20it%20was%20ultimately%20controlled%20by%20the%20interests%20of%20scientists%20who%20worried%20that%20the%20company's%20expansion%20was%20out%20of%20control%2C%20maybe%20even%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20put%20the%20scientists%20at%20odds%20with%20Altman%20and%20Brockman%2C%20who%20both%20argued%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20growing%20its%20business%20out%20of%20necessity.%20Every%20time%20a%20customer%20asks%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20chatbot%20a%20question%20it%20requires%20huge%20amounts%20of%20expensive%20computing%20power%20-%20so%20much%20that%20the%20company%20was%20having%20trouble%20keeping%20up%20with%20the%20explosive%20demand%20from%20users.%20The%20company%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20place%20limits%20on%20the%20number%20of%20times%20users%20can%20query%20its%20most%20powerful%20AI%20models%20in%20a%20day.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20situation%20got%20so%20dire%20in%20the%20days%20after%20the%20developer%20conference%2C%20Altman%20announced%20that%20the%20company%20was%20pausing%20sign-ups%20for%20its%20paid%20ChatGPT%20Plus%20service%20for%20an%20indeterminate%20amount%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20Altman's%20point%20of%20view%2C%20raising%20more%20money%20and%20finding%20additional%20revenue%20sources%20were%20essential.%20But%20some%20members%20of%20the%20board%2C%20with%20ties%20to%20the%20AI-skeptical%20effective%20altruism%20movement%2C%20viewed%20this%20in%20tension%20with%20the%20risks%20posed%20by%20advanced%20AI.%20Many%20effective%20altruists%20-%20a%20pseudo-philosophical%20movement%20that%20seeks%20to%20donate%20money%20to%20head%20off%20existential%20risks%20-%20have%20imagined%20scenarios%20in%20which%20a%20powerful%20AI%20system%20could%20be%20used%20by%20a%20terrorist%20group%20to%2C%20say%2C%20create%20a%20bioweapon.%20Or%20in%20the%20absolute%20worst-case%20scenario%20the%20AI%20could%20spontaneously%20turn%20bad%2C%20take%20control%20of%20weapons%20systems%20and%20attempt%20to%20wipe%20out%20human%20civilization.%20Not%20everyone%20takes%20this%20scenario%20seriously%2C%20and%20other%20AI%20leaders%2C%20including%20Altman%2C%20have%20argued%20that%20such%20concerns%20can%20be%20managed%20and%20that%20the%20potential%20benefits%20from%20making%20AI%20broadly%20available%20outweighs%20the%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%20though%2C%20the%20skeptics%20won%20out%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20famous%20living%20founders%20was%20suddenly%20relieved%20of%20duty.%20Adding%20to%20the%20sense%20of%20chaos%2C%20the%20board%20made%20little%20effort%20to%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20transition.%20In%20its%20statement%20announcing%20the%20decision%2C%20the%20board%20implied%20that%20Altman%20had%20been%20dishonest%20-%20%26quot%3Bnot%20consistently%20candid%20in%20his%20communications%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20in%20its%20explosive%20announcement.%20The%20board%20didn't%20specify%20any%20dishonesty%20and%20OpenAI%20Chief%20Operating%20Officer%20Brad%20Lightcap%20later%20said%20in%20a%20memo%20to%20employees%20that%20it%20was%20not%20accusing%20Altman%20of%20malfeasance%2C%20chalking%20his%20removal%20up%20not%20to%20a%20debate%20over%20safety%2C%20but%20a%20%26quot%3Bbreakdown%20in%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20had%20also%20moved%20without%20consulting%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20leaving%20Nadella%20%26quot%3Blivid%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20hasty%20termination%20of%20a%20crucial%20business%20partner%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20his%20thinking.%20Nadella%20was%20%26quot%3Bblindsided%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20news%2C%20this%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20his%20plans%2C%20Altman%20was%20plotting%20a%20competing%20company%2C%20while%20investors%20were%20agitating%20for%20his%20restoration.%20Over%20the%20weekend%2C%20some%20investors%20were%20considering%20writing%20down%20the%20value%20of%20their%20OpenAI%20holdings%20to%20zero%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20move%2C%20which%20would%20both%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20company%20to%20raise%20additional%20funds%20and%20allow%20OpenAI%20investors%20to%20back%20Altman's%20theoretical%20competitor%2C%20seemed%20designed%20to%20pressure%20the%20board%20to%20resign%20and%20bring%20Altman%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20on%20Saturday%20night%2C%20numerous%20OpenAI%20executives%20and%20dozens%20of%20employees%20started%20tweeting%20the%20heart%20emoji%20-%20a%20statement%20of%20solidarity%20that%20appeared%20equal%20parts%20an%20expression%20of%20love%20for%20Altman%20and%20a%20rebuke%20to%20the%20board.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20familiar%20with%20Nadella's%20thinking%20said%20that%20the%20Microsoft%20CEO%20was%20advocating%20for%20Altman's%20potential%20return%20and%20would%20also%20be%20interested%20in%20backing%20Altman's%20new%20venture.%20The%20source%20predicted%20that%20if%20the%20board%20doesn't%20reconsider%2C%20a%20large%20continent%20of%20OpenAI%20engineers%20would%20likely%20resign%20in%20the%20company%20days.%20Adding%20to%20the%20sense%20of%20uncertainty%3A%20OpenAI's%20offices%20are%20closed%20all%20this%20week.%20Microsoft%20and%20Altman%20declined%20to%20comment.%20When%20reached%20by%20phone%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Brockman%2C%20who%20resigned%20shortly%20after%20Altman%20was%20fired%2C%20said%20%26quot%3BSuper%20heads%20down%20right%20now%2C%20sorry.%26quot%3B%20Then%20he%20hung%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20philosophical%20disagreement%20wouldn't%20normally%20doom%20a%20company%20that%20had%20been%20in%20talks%20to%20sell%20shares%20to%20investors%20at%20an%20%C2%A0%2486%20billion%20valuation%2C%20but%20OpenAI%20was%20nothing%20like%20a%20normal%20company.%20Altman%20structured%20it%20as%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20with%20a%20for-profit%20subsidiary%20that%20he%20ran%20and%20that%20had%20aggressively%20courted%20venture%20capitalists%20and%20corporate%20partners.%20The%20novel%20-%20and%2C%20as%20OpenAI%20critics%20see%20it%2C%20flawed%20-%20structure%20put%20Altman%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20all%20of%20the%20company's%20customers%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20a%20wonky%20board%20of%20directors%20that%20was%20dominated%20by%20those%20who%20were%20skeptical%20of%20the%20corporate%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20original%20goal%2C%20when%20it%20was%20founded%20by%20a%20team%20including%20Altman%20and%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20was%20to%20%26quot%3Badvance%20digital%20intelligence%20in%20the%20way%20that%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20benefit%20humanity%20as%20a%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20a%202015%20announcement%20put%20it.%20The%20organization%20wouldn't%20pursue%20financial%20gain%20for%20its%20own%20sake%2C%20but%20would%20instead%20serve%20as%20a%20check%20on%20profit-minded%20efforts%2C%20ensuring%20that%20AI%20would%20be%20developed%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20extension%20of%20individual%20human%20wills%20and%2C%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20liberty%2C%20as%20broadly%20and%20evenly%20distributed%20as%20is%20possible%20safely.%26quot%3B%20Musk%2C%20who%20had%20been%20warning%20about%20the%20risks%20that%20an%20out%20of%20control%20AI%20system%20might%20pose%20to%20humanity%2C%20provided%20much%20of%20the%20nonprofit's%20initial%20funding.%20Other%20backers%20included%20the%20investor%20Peter%20Thiel%20and%20LinkedIn%20co-founder%20Reid%20Hoffman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20Musk%20helped%20recruit%20Ilya%20Sutskever%20as%20the%20company's%20chief%20scientist.%20The%20hiring%20was%20a%20coup.%20Sutskever%20is%20a%20legend%20in%20the%20field%20dating%20back%20to%20his%20research%20on%20neural%20networks%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%2C%20and%20continuing%20at%20Google%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20at%20the%20company's%20Google%20Brain%20lab.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20podcast%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20Musk%20said%20he%20had%20decided%20to%20fund%20OpenAI%20and%20had%20personally%20recruited%20Sutskever%20away%20from%20Google%20because%20he'd%20gotten%20worried%20that%20the%20search%20giant%20was%20developing%20AI%20without%20regard%20for%20safety.%20Musk's%20hope%20was%20to%20slow%20Google%20down.%20Musk%20added%20that%20recruiting%20Sutskever%20ended%20his%20friendship%20with%20Google%20co-founder%20Larry%20Page.%20But%20Musk%20himself%20later%20became%20estranged%20from%20Altman%2C%20leaving%20OpenAI%20in%202018%20and%20cutting%20it%20off%20from%20further%20funding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAltman%20needed%20money%2C%20and%20venture%20capital%20firms%20and%20big%20tech%20companies%20were%20interested%20in%20backing%20ambitious%20AI%20efforts.%20To%20tap%20that%20pool%20of%20capital%2C%20he%20created%20a%20new%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20nonprofit%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcapped%20profit%26quot%3B%20company.%20OpenAI's%20for-profit%20arm%20would%20raise%20money%20from%20investors%2C%20but%20promised%20that%20if%20its%20profits%20reached%20a%20certain%20level%20-%20initially%20100%20times%20the%20investment%20of%20early%20backers%20-%20anything%20above%20that%20would%20be%20donated%20back%20to%20the%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20position%20as%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Altman%20has%20said%20he%20holds%20no%20equity%20in%20the%20company%2C%20framing%20this%20as%20of%20a%20piece%20with%20the%20company's%20philanthropic%20mission.%20But%20of%20course%2C%20this%20would-be%20philanthropy%20had%20also%20sold%2049%25%20of%20its%20equity%20to%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20was%20granted%20no%20seats%20on%20its%20board.%20In%20an%20interview%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Altman%20suggested%20that%20the%20only%20recourse%20Microsoft%20had%20to%20control%20the%20company%20would%20be%20to%20unplug%20the%20servers%20that%20OpenAI%20rented.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20they%20will%20honor%20their%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ultimate%20power%20at%20the%20company%20rested%20with%20the%20board%2C%20which%20included%20Altman%2C%20Sutskever%20and%20president%20Greg%20Brockman.%20The%20other%20members%20were%20Quora%20Inc.%20CEO%20Adam%20D'Angelo%2C%20tech%20entrepreneur%20Tasha%20McCauley%20and%20Helen%20Toner%2C%20director%20of%20strategy%20at%20Georgetown's%20Center%20for%20Security%20and%20Emerging%20Technology.%20McCauley%20and%20Toner%20both%20had%20ties%20to%20effective%20altruism%20nonprofits.%20Toner%20had%20previously%20worked%20for%20Open%20Philanthropy%3B%20McCauley%20serves%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20Effective%20Ventures%20and%2080%2C000%20Hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20isn't%20the%20only%20ambitious%20technology%20project%20situated%20inside%20a%20nonprofit.%20The%20web%20browser%20Mozilla%2C%20the%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20and%20the%20operating%20system%20Linux%20are%20all%20developed%20by%20nonprofits%2C%20and%20before%20selling%20his%20company%20to%20Musk%2C%20Twitter%20co-founder%20Jack%20Dorsey%20lamented%20that%20the%20social%20network%20was%20beholden%20to%20investors.%20But%20open%20source%20projects%20are%20notoriously%20hard%20to%20govern%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20was%20operating%20at%20a%20greater%20scale%20and%20ambition%20than%20any%20tech%20nonprofit%20that%20had%20come%20before%20it.%20This%2C%20along%20with%20reports%20of%20the%20company's%20extreme%20financial%20success%2C%20created%20a%20backlash%20that%20was%20almost%20inevitable%20in%20retrospect.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Musk%20complained%20on%20X%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20no%20longer%20%26quot%3Ba%20counterweight%20to%20Google%2C%20but%20now%20it%20has%20become%20a%20closed%20source%2C%20maximum-profit%20company%20effectively%20controlled%20by%20Microsoft.%26quot%3B%20He%20reiterated%20these%20gripes%20during%20a%20recent%20appearance%20on%20Lex%20Fridman's%20podcast%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20company's%20pursuit%20of%20profit%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20good%20karma.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Altman%20was%20pursuing%20side%20projects%20that%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20enrich%20him%20and%20his%20investors%2C%20but%20which%20were%20outside%20of%20the%20control%20of%20OpenAI's%20safety-conscious%20board.%20There%20was%20Worldcoin%2C%20his%20eyeball-scanning%20crypto%20project%2C%20which%20launched%20in%20July%20and%20was%20promoted%20as%20a%20potential%20universal%20basic%20income%20system%20to%20make%20up%20for%20AI-related%20job%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAltman%20also%20explored%20starting%20his%20own%20AI%20chipmaker%2C%20pitching%20sovereign%20wealth%20funds%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20on%20an%20investment%20that%20could%20reach%20into%20the%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20plan.%20He%20also%20pitched%20SoftBank%20Group%20Corp.%2C%20led%20by%20Japanese%20billionaire%20and%20tech%20investor%20Masayoshi%20Son%2C%20on%20a%20potential%20multibillion-dollar%20investment%20in%20a%20company%20he%20planned%20to%20start%20with%20former%20Apple%20design%20guru%20Jony%20Ive%20to%20make%20AI-oriented%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20efforts%2C%20along%20with%20the%20for-profit's%20growing%20success%2C%20put%20Altman%20at%20odds%20with%20Sutskever%2C%20who%20was%20becoming%20more%20vocal%20about%20safety%20concerns.%20In%20July%2C%20Sutskever%20formed%20a%20new%20team%20within%20the%20company%20focused%20on%20reining%20in%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20intelligent%26quot%3B%20AI%20systems%20of%20the%20future.%20Tensions%20with%20Altman%20intensified%20in%20October%2C%20when%2C%20according%20to%20a%20source%20familiar%20with%20the%20relationship%2C%20Altman%20moved%20to%20reduce%20Sutskever's%20role%20at%20the%20company%2C%20which%20rubbed%20Sutskever%20the%20wrong%20way%20and%20spilled%20over%20into%20tension%20with%20the%20company's%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20event%20on%20Nov.%206%2C%20Altman%20made%20a%20number%20of%20announcements%20that%20infuriated%20Sutskever%20and%20people%20sympathetic%20to%20his%20point%20of%20view%2C%20the%20source%20said.%20Among%20them%3A%20customized%20versions%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20allowing%20anyone%20to%20create%20chatbots%20that%20would%20perform%20specialized%20tasks.%20OpenAI%20has%20said%20that%20it%20would%20eventually%20allow%20these%20custom%20GPTs%20to%20operate%20on%20their%20own%20once%20a%20user%20creates%20them.%20Similar%20autonomous%20agents%20are%20offered%20by%20competing%20companies%20but%20are%20a%20red%20flag%20for%20safety%20advocates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20that%20followed%2C%20Sutskever%20brought%20his%20concerns%20to%20the%20board.%20According%20to%20an%20account%20posted%20on%20X%20by%20Brockman%2C%20Sutskever%20texted%20Altman%20the%20evening%20of%20Nov.%2016%2C%20inviting%20him%20to%20join%20a%20video%20call%20with%20the%20board%20the%20following%20day.%20Brockman%20was%20not%20invited.%20The%20following%20day%20at%20noon%2C%20Altman%20appeared%20and%20was%20told%20he%20was%20being%20fired.%20Minutes%20later%2C%20the%20announcement%20went%20out%20and%20chaos%20followed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertainty%2C%20which%20continued%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20threatened%20OpenAI's%20elevated%20valuation%20and%20Microsoft's%20stock%20price%2C%20which%20dropped%20sharply%20as%20the%20market%20closed%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20disruption%20that%20could%20potentially%20slow%20down%20the%20rate%20of%20innovation%20and%20that's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20good%20for%20Microsoft%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rishi%20Jaluria%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20RBC%20Capital%20Markets.%20%26quot%3BOpenAI%20was%20going%20at%20breakneck%20speed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20companies%20that%20depend%20on%20OpenAI's%20software%20were%20hastily%20looking%20at%20competing%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20Meta%20Plaforms%20Inc.'s%20large%20language%20model%2C%20known%20as%20Llama.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20startup%2C%20we%20are%20worried%20now.%20Do%20we%20continue%20with%20them%20or%20not%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Amr%20Awadallah%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Vectara%2C%20which%20creates%20chatbots%20for%20corporate%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20choice%20to%20continue%20with%20OpenAI%20or%20seek%20out%20a%20competitor%20would%20depend%20on%20reassurances%20from%20the%20company%20and%20Microsoft.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20Microsoft%20to%20speak%20up%20and%20say%20everything%20is%20stable%2C%20we'll%20continue%20to%20focus%20on%20our%20customers%20and%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20Awadallah%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20hear%20something%20like%20that%20to%20restore%20our%20confidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Altman%20does%20get%20his%20job%20back%2C%20Musk%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20worried%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20posted%20on%20X%20on%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BIlya%20has%20a%20good%20moral%20compass%20and%20does%20not%20seek%20power.%20He%20would%20not%20take%20such%20drastic%20action%20unless%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20absolutely%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20