0parents%20should%20allow%20their%20kids%20to%20have%20is%20a%20long-running%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20researchers%20looked%20at%20over%2060%20studies%20from%201999%20to%202014%20on%20how%20screen%20time%20affects%20kids%2C%20they%20discovered%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1087079214000811%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20those%20studies%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20too%20much%20screen%20time%20was%20associated%20with%20poorer%20sleep.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamapediatrics%2Farticle-abstract%2F2722666%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20group%20of%20Canadian%20pediatricians%20%E2%80%94%20examining%20more%20than%202%2C400%20children%20aged%2024%20to%2036%20months%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0found%20that%20children%20who%20spent%20more%20time%20on%20screens%20tended%20to%20perform%20poorly%20on%20tests%20measuring%20early%20childhood%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aap.org%2Fen%2Fpatient-care%2Fmedia-and-children%2Fcenter-of-excellence-on-social-media-and-youth-mental-health%2Fsocial-media-and-youth-mental-health-q-and-a-portal%2Fmiddle-childhood%2Fmiddle-childhood-questions%2Fscreen-time-guidelines%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Academy%20of%20Pediatrics%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20there%20isn't%20enough%20evidence%20to%20support%20set%20screen%20time%20limits%2C%20which%20it%20stopped%20recommending%20as%20of%202016.%20Instead%2C%20the%20Academy%20now%20recommends%20rules%20focusing%20on%20avoiding%20particular%20types%20of%20content%20and%20parents%20watching%20content%20with%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipad-kids-tiktokers-worried-gen-z-millennials-gen-alpha-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700444183000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655436b036d588dc55d087f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipad-kids-tiktokers-worried-gen-z-millennials-gen-alpha-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20need%20everybody%20else%20from%20my%20generation%20to%20promise%20that%20we%20are%20not%20going%20to%20raise%20iPad%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20TikTok%20user%20%40gabesco.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kteo%40insider.com%20(Kai%20Xiang%20Teo)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipad-kids-tiktokers-worried-gen-z-millennials-gen-alpha-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Biden%20administration%20is%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20junk%20fees.%20Here's%20who's%20fighting%20to%20keep%20them.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22O'Hare%20Airport%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655aae754ca513d8242bffea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222042%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETravelers%20at%20Chicago%20O'Hare%20International%20Airport.%3Cp%3ETrent%20Sprague%2FChicago%20Tribune%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20earlier%20this%20year%20said%20his%20administration%20would%20crack%20down%20on%20hidden%20fees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20lobbyists%20are%20pushing%20back%20against%20proposed%20rules%20that%20could%20boost%20transparency%2C%20per%20WaPo.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWaPo%20examined%20federal%20lobbying%20files%20and%20hundreds%20of%20filings%20that%20were%20sent%20to%20federal%20agencies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20dizzying%20array%20of%20airline%20fees%20to%20add-ons%20tacked%20on%20to%20concert%20ticket%20prices%2C%20Americans%20are%20fed%20up%20with%20hidden%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20they%20have%20an%20ally%20in%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20who%20during%20his%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20address%20earlier%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhotel-resort-destination-fees-biden-opposition-amenities-cities-legislation-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evowed%20to%20crack%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20add-ons%2C%20often%20called%20junk%20fees%2C%20which%20when%20affixed%20to%20subtotals%20can%20make%20a%20simple%20hotel%20stay%20or%20a%20round-trip%20flight%20financially%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20wants%20to%20go%20after%20the%20practice%20and%20push%20companies%20to%20increase%20pricing%20transparency%20for%20consumer%20purchases%2C%20and%20his%20administration%20has%20targeted%20a%20swath%20of%20industries%20across%20the%20larger%20US%20economy%2C%20from%20airlines%20and%20ticket%20sales%20companies%20to%20banking%20institutions%20and%20credit%20card%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20corporations%20and%20their%20lobbyists%20are%20aggressively%20fighting%20back%20against%20proposed%20rules%20that%20would%20compel%20them%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%20about%20hidden%20fees%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F11%2F19%2Fcompanies-lobbyists-fight-junk-fees%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20analyzed%20federal%20lobbying%20files%20and%20filings%20sent%20to%20federal%20agencies%20as%20the%20administration%20pushes%20to%20save%20US%20consumers%20from%20collectively%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20fees%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20area%20where%20consumers%20have%20often%20lodged%20complaints%20is%20toward%20the%20airline%20industry.%20Travelers%20have%20long%20spoken%20out%20in%20favor%20of%20airlines%20revealing%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20tickets%20earlier%20in%20the%20sale%20process.%20And%20Biden%20wants%20airlines%20to%20oblige%20to%20what%20consumers%20have%20asked%20for%20regarding%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20major%20US-based%20airlines%2C%20including%20American%20Airlines%2C%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%2C%20and%20United%20Airlines%2C%20are%20not%20thrilled%20with%20the%20prospect%20of%20such%20a%20change%2C%20which%20consumers%20have%20advocated%20for%20in%20numerous%20letters%20submitted%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20(DOT).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20Mullen%2C%20the%20deputy%20general%20counsel%20at%20the%20lobbying%20group%20Airlines%20for%20America%2C%20said%20at%20a%20hearing%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20such%20a%20change%20would%20create%20%26quot%3Bconfusion%20and%20frustration%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20remarked%20that%20the%20DOT%20%26quot%3Bshould%20not%20regulate%20in%20this%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20for%20America%20lobbies%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20three%20aforementioned%20US%20air%20carriers%2C%20which%20transport%20millions%20of%20fliers%20domestically%20and%20internationally%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20DOT%2C%20the%20airline%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bts.gov%2Ftopics%2Fairlines-and-airports%2Fbaggage-fees-airline-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20%246.8%20billion%20in%20baggage%20fees%20in%202022.%20American%20Airlines%20collected%20almost%20%241.4%20billion%20in%20baggage%20fees%2C%20the%20domestic%20industry%20leader%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20The%20Post%2C%20the%20DOT%20has%20sought%20to%20create%20guidelines%20regarding%20how%20airlines%20should%20issue%20refunds%2C%20as%20well%20as%20rules%20for%20adding%20checked%20bag%20fees%20and%20tacking%20on%20change%20fees.%20But%20airlines%20have%20been%20critical%20of%20the%20efforts%2C%20with%20carriers%20stating%20that%20the%20department's%20proposals%20may%20be%20impractical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20concert%20fees%2C%20another%20sore%20spot%20for%20consumers%2C%20Live%20Nation%20executive%20vice%20president%20for%20corporate%20and%20regulatory%20affairs%20Dan%20Wall%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20company%20cannot%20create%20mandates%20for%20venues%20that%20it%20doesn't%20own.%20But%20he%20said%20that%20federal%20regulations%20on%20company%20disclosures%20would%20make%20certain%20that%20%26quot%3Beverybody%20does%20it%20so%20that%20nobody%20is%20disadvantaged%20for%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700444127000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655aaedd22cf74a57399e89b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Washington%20Post%20analyzed%20federal%20lobbying%20files%20as%20the%20administration%20works%20to%20save%20consumers%20from%20collectively%20paying%20billions%20in%20fees%20each%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A79%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20There%20Life%20After%20Electoral%20Bonds%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20introduced%20in%202017%2C%20Electoral%20Bonds%20(EBs)%20seem%20to%20have%20become%20a%20popular%20topic%20in%20the%20national%20discourse%20ever%20since%20the%20recent%20three-day%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC).%20There%20has%20been%20fair%20bit%20of%20writing%20in%20the%20print%20and%20digital%20media%2C%20and%20also%20some%20discussion%20on%20TV.%20In%20quite%20a%20few%20of%20media%20writings%20suggestions%20have%20been%20given%20on%20how%20to%20make%20EBs%20less%20opaque%20or%20confidential%20(as%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20kept%20insisting%20during%20the%20SC%20hearings).%20Quite%20a%20few%20correspondents%2Freporters%20have%20also%20asked%20me%20to%20specifically%20comment%20on%20how%20to%20make%20EBs%20%E2%80%9Cacceptable%E2%80%9D.%20That%20is%20what%20prompts%20the%20title%20of%20this%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20us%20seem%20to%20have%20forgotten%20that%20political%20parties%2C%20elections%20and%20democracy%20existed%20even%20before%202017%2C%20i.e.%2C%20before%20the%20introduction%20of%20EBs.%20Existence%20of%20political%20parties%20implies%20that%20parties%20got%20money%20to%20conduct%20their%20affairs%20including%20contesting%20elections%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20mystery%20where%20and%20how%20they%20got%20the%20money%20and%20from%20whom.%20There%20were%20several%20methods%20of%20political%20parties%20getting%20money%20such%20as%20(a)%20by%20cheque%2C%20(b)%20by%20bank%20draft%2C%20(c)%20by%20digital%20transfer%20through%20banks%2C%20(d)%20digital%20payment%20through%20apps%2C%20(e)%20Electoral%20Trusts%2C%20and%20(f)%20cash%2C%20with%20each%20donation%20being%20not%20more%20than%20Rs%202%2C000.%20The%20most%20popular%20method%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20cash%20in%20unlimited%20amounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI's%20Objections%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%5C%22%3EHow%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20Objections%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20complication%20was%2C%20and%20still%20is%2C%20that%20there%20was%20no%20incontrovertible%20proof%20of%20the%20transactions%20by%20the%20last%2C%20and%20the%20most%20common%2C%20method%20and%20therefore%20no%20one%20except%20the%20giver%20and%20the%20receiver%20knew%20how%20much%20money%20was%20given%20by%20whom%20and%20to%20whom.%20Some%20insiders%20and%20snoopers%20were%20of%20course%2C%20the%20expected%20exceptions.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20was%20not%20possible%20for%20people%20at%20large%20to%20know%20whether%20decisions%20by%20a%20particular%20political%20party%20in%20power%2C%20in%20the%20Centre%20of%20any%20of%20the%20States%2C%20were%20motivated%20by%20welfare%20of%20the%20people%20at%20large%20or%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20donor%20of%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20unaccounted%20cash.%20We%20also%20need%20to%20remember%20that%20donations%20need%20not%20be%20strictly%20only%20in%20cash%2C%20they%20can%20also%20be%20in%20kind%20such%20as%20making%20aircraft%20or%20helicopters%20booked%20in%20the%20name%20of%20some%20company%20or%20individual%2C%20being%20provided%20to%20a%20political%20party%20for%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20has%20claimed%20during%20the%20hearings%20in%20the%20SC%20that%20ever%20since%20EBs%20were%20introduced%20that%20transparency%20of%20electoral%20funding%20has%20improved%2C%20the%20statement%20made%20above%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cno%20one%20except%20the%20giver%20and%20the%20receiver%20knew%20how%20much%20money%20was%20given%20by%20whom%20and%20to%20whom%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20still%20valid%20with%20a%20very%20interesting%20change.%20Going%20strictly%20according%20to%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20as%20announced%20by%20the%20government%2C%20not%20even%20the%20receiver%20may%20know%20who%20has%20given%20the%20money!%20This%20of%20course%20is%20creative%20imagination%20of%20the%20highest%20order%20as%20everyone%20knows%20that%20one%20who%20gives%20money%20always%20makes%20sure%20the%20receiver%20knows%20who%20is%20the%20giver.%20The%20pious%20concept%20of%20%3Cem%3Egupt-daan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(anonymous%20donation)%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20political%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%2C%20and%20should%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20will%20refrain%20from%20suggesting%20what%20the%20SC%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20because%20the%20judgment%20is%20reserved%2C%20but%20being%20part%20of%20one%20of%20the%20petitioner-organisations%2C%20what%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20do%20is%20to%20declare%20Sections%20135%2C%20137%2C%2011%20and%20154%20of%20the%20Finance%20Act%202017%20and%20consequential%20amendments%20in%20Section%2031%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%201934%2C%20Section%2029C%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%201951%2C%20Section%2013A%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%201961%2C%20and%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%202013%3B%20and%20Section%20236%20of%20Finance%20Act%202016%20and%20consequential%20amendments%20in%20Section%202(1)(j)(vi)%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%202010%20%E2%80%9Cas%20being%20unconstitutional%2C%20null%20and%20void%E2%80%9D.%20What%20this%20legal%20jargon%20means%20is%20that%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20declare%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20as%20unconstitutional%20or%20illegal%2C%20or%20in%20even%20simpler%20words%20to%20strike%20it%20down.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we%20would%20like%20the%20SC%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20issue%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20SC%20do%3F%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20more%20important%20and%20needs%20some%20comment.%20A%20lot%20of%20commentary%20has%20suggested%20that%20the%20SC%20should%20make%20some%20modifications%20in%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20to%20remove%20what%20has%20been%20variously%20called%20as%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20disclosure%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20or%20partial%20transparency%E2%80%9D%20and%20of%20course%20the%20celebrated%20%E2%80%9Cpartial%20confidentiality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20go%20to%20some%20basics%20in%20order%20to%20resolve%20this%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20SC%20do%3F%E2%80%9D.%20Under%20the%20principle%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20the%20three%20pillars%20of%20the%20State%20%E2%80%93%20the%20legislature%2C%20the%20executive%20and%20the%20judiciary%20%E2%80%93%20have%20separate%20and%20distinct%20powers.%20In%20simple%20terms%2C%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20legislature%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Emake%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws%2C%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20executive%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Eimplement%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws%2C%20and%20the%20prime%20function%20of%20the%20judiciary%20is%20to%20%3Cem%3Einterpret%3C%2Fem%3E%20laws.%20The%20power%20to%20interpret%20laws%20implies%20and%20includes%20the%20power%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejudicial%20review%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20implies%20that%20the%20higher%20judiciary%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20high%20courts%20have%20the%20power%20to%20review%20any%20action%20of%20the%20legislature%20and%20the%20executive%20and%20decide%20whether%20these%20actions%20are%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20or%20not%2C%20and%20if%20they%20find%20any%20of%20the%20actions%20not%20to%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20high%20courts%20have%20the%20power%20to%20declare%20any%20such%20action%20as%20unconstitutional.%20That%20is%20why%20in%20our%20petition%20we%20have%20requested%20the%20SC%20to%20declare%20the%20above-mentioned%20laws%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%2C%20null%20and%20void%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Time%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftime-to-shut-the-floodgates-of-secret-political-party-funding%5C%22%3ETime%20to%20Shut%20the%20Floodgates%20of%20Secret%20Political%20Party%20Funding%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20maintain%20that%20all%20that%20the%20SC%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20do%20is%20to%20declare%20these%20laws%20as%20unconstitutional%20and%20no%20more.%20While%20many%20of%20the%20suggestions%20that%20have%20been%2C%20and%20are%20still%20being%20made%2C%20about%20what%20the%20SC%20should%20do%2C%20are%20valuable%20but%20they%20are%20all%20outside%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20SC.%20What%20must%20be%20remembered%20is%20that%20laws%20can%20be%20made%20only%20by%20the%20legislature.%20Yes%2C%20the%20SC%20can%20certainly%20make%20suggestions%2C%20%3Cem%3Eif%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20wishes%20to%20do%20that%2C%20but%20it%20cannot%2C%20in%20my%20view%2C%20make%20modifications%20to%20the%20scheme%20as%20enunciated%20by%20the%20government%20and%20passed%20by%20the%20Parliament.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20EBs%20scheme%20by%20the%20Parliament%20is%20also%20in%20doubt%20because%20it%20was%20included%20in%20a%20Money%20Bill%2C%20thus%20disabling%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20from%20making%20changes%20to%20it%20but%20that%20issue%20is%20being%20examined%20by%20a%20separate%20constitutional%20bench%20of%20seven%20judges%20and%20was%20therefore%20not%20argued%20before%20the%20current%20bench%20of%20five%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we%20just%20have%20to%20wait%20and%20see%20what%20the%20SC%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJagdeep%20S.%20Chhokar%20is%20a%20concerned%20citizen.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_edn2%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fis-there-life-after-electoral-bonds%23_ednref2%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700443834000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fis-there-life-after-elec