kers%20has%20not%20dramatically%20shifted%20from%20the%20early%202000s%3A%2060%20percent%20of%20students%20from%20this%20demographic%20group%20only%20earned%20a%201%20or%202%20out%20of%20a%20possible%205%20on%20the%20exam%2C%20which%20precludes%20them%20from%20earning%20college%20credit%20for%20the%20AP%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%2038%20percent%20of%20all%20test-takers%20scored%20a%201%20or%202%2C%20with%20low-income%20students%20posting%20higher%20failure%20rates.%20Yet%20taxpayers%20this%20year%20shelled%20out%20at%20least%20%2490%20million%20to%20pay%20for%20AP%20exams%20that%20a%20sizable%20percentage%20of%20students%20didn't%20pass%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2010%2F02%2F11%2Feducation%2F11college.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%2C%20based%20on%20its%20own%20analysis%20of%20College%20Board%20files%20and%20local%20education%20budgets%2C%20said%20that%20the%20organization%20receives%20about%20%24100%20million%20each%20year%20in%20public%20money%20for%20AP%20exams.%20In%20response%20to%20The%20Times%2C%20the%20College%20Board%20said%20that%20in%202023%2C%20it%20had%20received%20at%20least%20%2490%20million%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20cover%20exam%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20tax%20filings%2C%20the%20College%20Board%20stated%20that%20it%20took%20in%20roughly%20%245%20million%20to%20%246%20million%20in%20direct%20government%20funding%20each%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Harvard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655a46ad22cf74a57399e0c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20College%20Board%20argues%20that%20their%20push%20to%20expand%20AP%20boosts%20students%20from%20all%20backgrounds.%20Pictured%20is%20Harvard%20University%20in%20Cambridge%2C%20Massachusetts.%3Cp%3EScott%20Eisen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E'The%20best%20stuff%20in%20education'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%2498%20per%20exam%20for%20US%20test-takers%2C%20AP%20fees%20bring%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20the%20organization%2C%20and%20the%20push%20to%20enroll%20more%20low-income%20students%20into%20the%20program%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20where%20revenue%20from%20the%20SAT%20%E2%80%94%20the%20College%20Board%20test%20that%20in%20recent%20years%20has%20become%20optional%20for%20students%20applying%20to%20a%20swath%20of%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20has%20sharply%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20reported%20that%20from%202019%20to%202022%2C%20SAT%20revenue%20dropped%20from%20%24403.6%20million%20to%20%24289.2%20million%2C%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20test%20being%20less%20ubiquitous%20in%20the%20college%20admissions%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20College%20Board%20stands%20firmly%20behind%20its%20AP%20push%2C%20though%2C%20pointing%20to%20equity%20and%20the%20need%20to%20expand%20education%20opportunities%20for%20students%20who%20may%20not%20have%20been%20initially%20on%20a%20college%20coursework%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20the%20best%20stuff%20in%20education%20were%20not%20just%20for%20the%20best%20to%20distinguish%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20but%20could%20engage%20a%20much%20broader%20set%20of%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%20College%20Board%20chief%20executive%20David%20Coleman%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomny.fm%2Fshows%2Fground-control-parenting-with-carol-sutton-lewis%2Fhigh-school-less-stress-more-joy-with-david-colema%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eduring%20a%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20we%20holding%20it%20for%20some%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20College%20Board%2C%20reflecting%20on%20its%20own%20analysis%2C%20stated%20that%20AP%20coursework%20boosts%20students%20across%20the%20board%2C%20independent%20of%20their%20respective%20scores%20on%20the%20exam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20organization%20has%20made%20this%20argument%20as%20AP%20has%20morphed%20into%20its%20financial%20crown%20jewel.%20The%20program%20in%202022%20brought%20in%20nearly%20%24500%20million%20in%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20AP%20expansion%20has%20offered%20more%20opportunities%20to%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20students%2C%20questions%20remain%20regarding%20the%20actual%20preparedness%20of%20low-income%20students%2C%20as%20they%20often%20lack%20the%20funding%20to%20pay%20for%20expensive%20test%20preparation%20courses%20and%20may%20not%20have%20been%20exposed%20to%20as%20much%20high-level%20work%20as%20their%20upper-income%20peers%20before%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20a%20record%201.1%20million%20students%20from%20low-income%20households%20took%20AP%20exams%2C%20per%20The%20Times.%20It's%20a%20sharp%20increase%20from%202003%20when%20153%2C000%20low-income%20students%20took%20the%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%205.2%20million%20students%20sat%20down%20for%20AP%20exams%20in%202023%2C%20a%20more%20than%20threefold%20increase%20from%202002%2C%20when%201.6%20million%20students%20took%20the%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrevor%20Packer%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Advanced%20Placement%20program%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20the%20number%20of%20students%20taking%20on%20the%20intense%20AP%20curriculum%20and%20the%20push%20to%20find%20students%20who%20can%20perform%20well%20in%20the%20classes%20more%20than%20makes%20up%20for%20the%20low%20scores%20from%20many%20test-takers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20College%20Board%20said%20that%20the%20money%20it%20receives%20from%20the%20government%20%E2%80%94%20about%2018%20percent%20of%20its%20overall%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20was%20%26quot%3Bminimal%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20its%20operating%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20these%20are%20worthwhile%20investments%20in%20preparing%20all%20students%20for%20their%20futures%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20recognize%20that%20all%20students%20are%20not%20yet%20receiving%20equitable%20preparation%20for%20AP%20coursework%20and%20that%20such%20work%20requires%20addressing%20inequities%20that%20occur%20years%20prior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fap-exams-college-board-taxpayers-college-prep-millions-test-fees-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700418412000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655a45df22cf74a57399e0b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fap-exams-college-board-taxpayers-college-prep-millions-test-fees-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20based%20on%20its%20own%20estimates%2C%20said%20that%20the%20College%20Board%20receives%20roughly%20%24100%20million%20each%20year%20in%20public%20money%20for%20AP%20exam%20fees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fap-exams-college-board-taxpayers-college-prep-millions-test-fees-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22X%E2%80%99s%20Unique%20Un-Sales%20Strategy%3A%20CEO%20Linda%20Yaccarino%20Woos%20Advertisers%3B%20Owner%20Elon%20Musk%20Drives%20Them%20Away%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700418000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FYaccarino-Musk-Possible-Conference-Miami.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235799512%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20movie%20and%20TV%20studios%20get%20nervous%20about%20advertising%2C%20so%20should%20everyone%20else.%20Advertisers%20loathe%20controversy%2C%20and%20often%20%E2%80%9Cpull%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cyank%E2%80%9D%20their%20commercial