ing%20to%20Napoleon%20Bonaparte%20has%20sold%20at%20auction%20in%20France%20for%20an%20estimate-busting%20%E2%82%AC1.9m%20(%C2%A31.69m).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A42%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fhat-belonging-to-napoleon-fetches-record-amount-at-auction-in-france-13011668%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fhat-belonging-to-napoleon-fetches-record-amount-at-auction-in-france-13011668%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fhat-belonging-to-napoleon-fetches-record-amount-at-auction-in-france-13011668%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahua%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20Plight%20Is%20Testament%20to%20the%20Kismet%20of%20Women%20Politicians%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19194524%2FF8yrxWKa0AAYIV9.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20parliament%20finally%20passed%20a%20law%20reserving%20one-third%20of%20total%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20and%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20every%20state%2C%20the%20targeting%20of%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20unsubstantiated%20charges%20is%20a%20reminder%20of%20how%20%E2%80%98gender%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98performance%20of%20femininity%E2%80%99%20shape%20the%20life%20of%20women%20leaders%20across%20the%20political%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20observe%20the%20statistics%20first.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2Frs%2Fmembers%5C%22%3ERajya%20Sabha%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20only%2031%20women%20among%20239%20total%20members%20and%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F164.100.47.194%2Floksabha%2FMembers%2Fwomen.aspx%5C%22%3ELok%20Sabha%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%2082%20of%20the%20539%20members%20are%20women.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.india.gov.in%2Fmy-government%2Fwhos-who%2Fcouncil-ministers%5C%22%3EGovernment%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%2010%20women%20find%20representation%20in%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%2079-member%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20out%20of%20which%20only%20two%20hold%C2%A0%20cabinet%20rank.%20The%20picture%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetail.aspx%3FPRID%3D1882226%5C%22%3Estate%20level%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20bleaker%2C%20with%20the%20national%20average%20of%20women%20in%20state%20assemblies%20being%20around%209%25.%20India%E2%80%99s%20rank%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_GGGR_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%E2%80%99s%20Global%20Gender%20Gap%20Index%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20127%20out%20of%20146%2C%20with%20the%20country%20trailing%20behind%20neighbours%20like%20Bangladesh%2C%20Nepal%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20general%20election%2C%20out%20of%20the%20435%20candidates%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20fielded%2C%2012.6%25%20were%20women.%20Women%20constituted%2012.9%25%20of%20the%20total%20candidates%20fielded%20by%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20some%20regional%20parties%E2%80%99%20selection%20of%20women%20candidates%20was%20quite%20commendable.%20Of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20candidates%20fielded%20by%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20All-India%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%2037.1%25%20were%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvidently%2C%20what%20are%20typically%20viewed%20as%20%E2%80%98gender%20neutral%E2%80%99%20public%20institutions%20and%20political%20parties%20in%20India%20are%20exclusively%20%E2%80%98for%2C%20by%20and%20of%E2%80%99%20men.%20Rather%2C%20%E2%80%98masculinity%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20defining%20feature%20of%20Indian%20politics.%20On%20its%20own%2C%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Act%2C%202023%20cannot%20enable%20greater%20political%20participation%20of%20women%20and%20their%20equal%20representation%20in%20parliament%20and%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Treatment%20of%20Mahua%20Moitra%20Is%20a%20Case%20Study%20on%20Gender%2C%20Power%20and%20Politics%20in%20India%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-treatment-of-mahua-moitra-is-a-case-study-on-gender-power-and-politics-in-india%5C%22%3EThe%20Treatment%20of%20Mahua%20Moitra%20Is%20a%20Case%20Study%20on%20Gender%2C%20Power%20and%20Politics%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Futorontopress.com%2F9781487525200%2Fwomen-power-and-political-representation%2F%5C%22%3Ebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20%3Cem%3EWomen%2C%20Power%2C%20and%20Political%20Representation%3A%20Canadian%20and%20Comparative%20Perspectives%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20authors%20have%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20introduction%20of%20gender%20quotas%20has%20improved%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20Canadian%20politics.%20However%2C%20Canadian%20women%20still%20face%20many%20informal%20and%20formal%20barriers%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20when%20they%20seek%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20political%20power%20but%20also%20once%20they%20have%20gained%20that%20power.%20They%20have%20cautioned%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%20need%20not%20just%20be%20present%20in%20politics%2C%20but%20rather%20should%20have%20access%20to%20key%20positions%20of%20power%20where%20they%20can%20act%20as%20gatekeepers%2C%20agenda%20setters%2C%20and%20political%20insiders%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Moitra%20matter%20reinforces%20the%20same%20lesson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20politics%20has%20constructed%20a%20sexual%20imagery%20of%20women%20leaders%20that%20primarily%20focuses%20on%20their%20character%2C%20physical%20appearance%2C%20dress%2C%20demeanour%20and%20family.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fwomen-politicians-face-sexism-and-misogynism-in-the-boys-club%2F%5C%22%3EThey%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20closely%20watched%20and%20their%20performance%20minutely%20scrutinised.%20While%20their%20success%20is%20understated%20and%20mostly%20shoved%20under%20the%20carpet%2C%20their%20failure%20is%20wholly%20attributed%20to%20their%20gender.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20news%20reporting%20on%20women%20MPs%20like%20Moitra%20is%20pervaded%20by%20gendered%20perceptions%20of%20ambition%2C%20visibility%2C%20competitiveness%2C%20suitability%20and%20capability.%20Her%20association%20with%20a%20leading%20businessman%20and%20fight%20with%20an%20ex-lover%20over%20Henry%2C%20their%20pet%20dog%2C%20have%20become%20more%20newsworthy%20than%20her%20attendance%20and%20performance%20in%20parliament.%20Conversely%2C%20her%20participation%20in%20parliamentary%20debates%2C%20the%20type%20of%20questions%20she%20has%20raised%2C%20and%20the%20veracity%20of%20her%20criticisms%20of%20the%20kleptocratic%20tendencies%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20have%20been%20largely%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20those%20pillorying%20Moitra%20have%20bothered%20to%20analyse%20how%20many%20of%20questions%20she%20has%20raised%20in%20Parliament%20have%20a%20direct%20link%20with%20her%20businessman%20friend%2C%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20whose%20office%20staff%20helped%20her%20upload%20those%20questions.%20When%20it%20is%20common%20practice%20for%20MPs%20to%20share%20their%20login%20details%20and%20even%20one-time-passwords%20(OTPs)%20with%20personal%20assistants%2C%20office%20staff%2C%20policy%20clerks%2C%20interns%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20the%20authors%20and%20almost%20all%20LAMP%20fellows%20who%20have%20worked%20with%20MPs%20from%20different%20political%20parties%20will%20easily%20vouch%20for%20this%20fact%20%E2%80%93%20why%20is%20Mahua%20Moitra%20being%20singled%20out%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lok%20Sabha%20Ethics%20Committee%2C%20which%20was%20established%20in%202015%20to%20oversee%20the%20moral%20and%20ethical%20conduct%20of%20members%20and%20examine%20cases%20of%20misconduct%20referred%20to%20it%2C%20has%20been%20operating%20without%20a%20proper%20written%20%E2%80%98Code%20of%20Conduct%20for%20Members%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20mandatory%20%E2%80%98Declaration%20of%20Members%E2%80%99%20Business%20Interests%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20highly%20probable%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20these%20two%20important%20documents%2C%20the%20committee%20can%20cherry-pick%20cases%20involving%20MPs%20from%20opposition%20parties%20while%20going%20easy%20with%20ruling%20party%20members.%20Further%2C%20the%20committee%20can%20also%20conduct%20hearings%20without%20following%20a%20fair%2C%20just%20and%20impartial%20procedure%20%E2%80%93%20as%20was%20seen%20in%20the%20Moitra%20matter%2C%20where%20she%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20cross-examine%20those%20who%20had%20levelled%20grave%20charges%20against%20her.%20This%20violates%20the%20norms%20of%20natural%20justice%20in%20a%20constitutional%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmahua-moitra-ramesh-bidhuri-very-different-parliament-committee%5C%22%3Enot%20escaped%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20notice%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20committee%20has%20been%20super%20swift%20to%20investigate%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20association%20with%20Hiranandani.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20its%20response%20has%20been%20extremely%20tardy%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20BJP%20MP%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%20who%20made%20communal%20and%20sexist%20comments%20against%20several%20MPs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Framesh-bidhuri-danish-ali-lok-sabha-hate-speech%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Danish%20Ali%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20avert%20sexual%20objectification%2C%20increase%20their%20acceptability%20within%20politics%20and%20be%20%E2%80%98likeable%E2%80%99%20among%20the%20masses%2C%20women%20leaders%20have%20taken%20to%20supposedly%20asexual%2C%20respectable%20and%20dignified%20titles%20like%20%E2%80%98Didi%E2%80%99%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20(elder%20sister)%2C%20%E2%80%98Behenji%E2%80%99%20Mayawati%20(sister)%2C%20%E2%80%98Amma%E2%80%99%20Jayalalitha%20(mother).%20Even%20Moitra%20has%20chanted%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Ma%20Durga%E2%80%99%20and%20invoked%20the%20powerful%20Hindu%20goddess%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMahuaMoitra%2Fstatus%2F1715080166870004009%5C%22%3EX%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fight%20off%20the%20attacks%20on%20herself%20from%20the%20BJP.%20We%20cannot%20forget%20that%20as%20a%20woman%20politician%2C%20she%20has%20to%20work%20over%20time%20to%20not%20let%20the%20scandal%20blight%20her%20political%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Mahua%20Moitra%20and%20the%20Question%20of%20Maryada%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmahua-moitra-and-the-question-of-maryada%5C%22%3EMahua%20Moitra%20and%20the%20Question%20of%20Maryada%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20there%20exists%20zero%20female%20sorority%20in%20Indian%20politics.%20Women%20politicians%20do%20not%20get%20the%20requisite%20support%20from%20peers%20in%20their%20own%20political%20party%2C%20nor%20are%20formal%20institutional%20mechanisms%20available%20to%20check%20misogyny%20and%20bullying.%20When%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20quizzed%20MP%20Moitra%20about%20her%20private%20life%2C%20none%20of%20the%20women%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20responded.%20Women%20leaders%20find%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20support%20their%20ilk%20across%20party%20lines%20because%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20reconcile%20their%20gender%20identity%20and%20political%20differences.%20Explaining%20the%20reality%20of%20female%20misogyny%2C%20feminist%20writer%20Chimamanda%20Adichie%20has%20commented%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BA%5Dnd%20there%20are%20many%20women%20in%20the%20world%20who%20do%20not%20like%20other%20women.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20writ%20large%20in%20Indian%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIreland%E2%80%99s%20landmark%202009%20report%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.oireachtas.ie%2Fie%2Foireachtas%2Fcommittee%2Fdail%2F32%2Fjoint_committee_on_justice_and_equality%2Freports%2F2009%2F2009-11-05_women-s-participation-in-politics_en.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Women%E2%80%99s%20Participation%20in%20Politics%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20factors%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98less%20confidence%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98gendered%20culture%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98gender%20bias%20in%20political%20parties%E2%80%99%20in%20candidate%E2%80%99s%20selection%20procedures%E2%80%99%20adversely%20affect%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.womenforelection.ie%2Fpdfs%2F5Cs-Scorecard-assessing-progress-in-the-wake-of-the-2009-Womens-Participation-in-Politics-report.pdf%5C%22%3Epoliticians%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Particularly%20in%20India%2C%20because%20the%20Parliament%2C%20state%20assemblies%20and%20political%20parties%20are%20mainly%20led%20and%20run%20by%20men%2C%20the%20culture%20of%20behaviour%20and%20the%20informally%20accepted%20norms%20of%20language%2C%20views%20and%20expressions%20render%20the%20political%20sphere%20unsuitable%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoitra%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20as%20a%20mark%20of%20protest%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3Elashed%20out%20against%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20unfair%20procedure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20manner%20of%20investigation%20and%20content%20of%20the%20questions.%20While%20people%20were%20left%20aghast%20at%20her%20audacity%2C%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20has%20called%20her%20remarks%20%E2%80%98explosive%E2%80%99.%20Kimberle%20Crenshaw%E2%80%99s%20words%20can%20be%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20Indian%20society%20for%20which%20%E2%80%9Csaving%20honour%20from%20shame%20is%20a%20priority.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20priority%20tends%20to%20be%20more%20readily%20interpreted%20as%20obliging%20women%20not%20to%20scream%20rather%20than%20obliging%20men%20not%20to%20hit%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20such%20a%20deep-seated%20culture%20of%20misogyny%2C%20what%20will%20it%20take%20for%20Indian%20lawmakers%20to%20remodel%20Parliament%20into%20a%20truly%20diverse%2C%20inclusive%20and%20accommodating%20place%20of%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrerna%20Dhoop%20is%20an%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%20(NLSIU)%20Bangalore%20and%20Vandana%20Dhoop%20teaches%20at%20the%20St.%20Xavier%E2%80%99s%20University%2C%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700403374000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19194524%2FF8yrxWKa0AAYIV9.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmahua-moitras-plight-is-testament-to-the-kismet-of-women-politicians-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian%20politics%20has%20constructed%20a%20sexual%20imagery%20of%20women%20leaders%20that%20primarily%20focuses%20on%20their%20character%2C%20physical%20appearance%2C%20dress%2C%20demeanour%20and%20family.%20While%20their%20success%20is%20understated%20and%20mostly%20shoved%20under%20the%20carpet%2C%20their%20failure%20is%20wholly%20attributed%20to%20their%20gender.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fmahua-moitras-plight-is-testament-to-the-kismet-of-women-politicians-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20than%20a%20foot%20of%20snow%2C%20100%20mph%20wind%20gusts%20possible%20as%20storm%20approaches%20Sierra%20Nevada%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700402713000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105335073%2Cimgsize-1033918.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmore-than-a-foot-of-snow-100-mph-wind-gusts-possible-as-storm-approaches-sierra-nevada%2Farticleshow%2F105335031.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105335031.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmore-than-a-foot-of-snow-100-mph-wind-gusts-possible-as-storm-approaches-sierra-nevada%2Farticleshow%2F105335031.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmore-than-a-foot-of-snow-100-mph-wind-gusts-possible-as-storm-approaches-sierra-nevada%2Famp_articleshow%2F105335031.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmore-than-a-foot-of-snow-100-mph-wind-gusts-possible-as-storm-approaches-sierra-nevada%2Famp_articleshow%2F105335031.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Do%20US%20Sanctions%20on%20Russia's%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20Project%20Mean%20for%20the%20World%20Energy%20Order%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19192144%2Fbelokameka-LNG-center.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20bouts%20of%20sanctions%20the%20United%20States%20recently%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20apparently%20signal%20a%20strategic%20shift%20in%20the%20world%20energy%20order.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Ftaking-additional-sweeping-measures-against-russia%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Arctic%20liquefied%20national%20gas%20(LNG)%202%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20imposed%20as%20a%20penalty%20for%20its%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20have%20different%20ramifications.%20Insofar%20as%20a%20new%20geopolitical%20dynamic%20takes%20shape%20in%20the%20already%20volatile%20Arctic%20region%2C%20Washington%20appears%20determined%20to%20prevent%20Russia%20from%20gaining%20prominence%20in%20the%20global%20energy%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20the%20emerging%20strategic%20landscape%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20continuing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20new%20spell%20of%20war%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20%E2%80%93%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20international%20correlation%20of%20power%20dynamic%2C%20with%20all%20its%20attendant%20implications%20for%20the%20global%20energy%20supply%20chains%3F%20Though%20it%20is%20too%20early%20to%20suggest%20a%20quick%20revival%2Freversal%20in%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20the%20global%20market%20is%20expected%20to%20grapple%20with%20disruptions%20and%20shortfalls%20in%20the%20energy%20sector%2C%20in%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%20Perceptibly%2C%20the%20United%20States%20is%20poised%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20and%20dictate%20the%20terms%20of%20energy%20trade%20in%20the%20coming%20decades.%20The%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20precursor%20of%20this%20changing%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F03%2F03%2Fceraweek-how-russias-war-made-the-us-a-dominant-supplier-of-energy-.html%5C%22%3Ereshaped%20global%20energy%20supply%20chains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20propelling%20the%20US%20to%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20energy-exporting%20nations.%20As%20Europe%20faced%20challenges%20in%20its%20natural%20gas%20imports%20from%20Russia%2C%20US%20exporters%20redirected%20shipments%20of%20LNG%20from%20Asia%20to%20Europe.%20With%20Russian%20oil%20under%20sanctions%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20rejecting%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20seaborne%20cargoes%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20US%20crude%20and%20refined%20product%20exports%20to%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20marked%20a%20significant%20transformation%2C%20with%20the%20US%20evolving%20from%20a%20supplier%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmilitary%20arsenal%E2%80%9D%20to%20a%20major%20energy%20arsenal%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F03%2F03%2Fceraweek-how-russias-war-made-the-us-a-dominant-supplier-of-energy-.html%5C%22%3Enoted%20by%20John%20Kilduff%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Again%20Capital.%20Already%2C%20indications%20in%20this%20direction%20have%20come%20from%20US%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fdigital-press-briefing-with-geoffrey-r-pyatt-assistant-secretary-of-state-for-energy-resources%2F%5C%22%3Especial%20briefing%20on%20October%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Geoffrey%20R.%20Pyatt%2C%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20state%20for%20energy%20resources%2C%20said%20that%20the%20US%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccommitted%20to%20working%20in%20lockstep%20both%20to%20impose%20a%20price%20on%20Russia%20for%20its%20brutal%20invasion%2C%20but%20also%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20deny%20Putin%20the%20resources%20that%20he%20is%20using%20in%20order%20to%20prosecute%20this%20terrible%20war%20against%20the%20people%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D.%20And%20in%20the%20case%20of%20its%20G7%20partners%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20US%20is%20%E2%80%9Calso%20committed%20to%20working%20jointly%20to%20deny%20Russia%20future%20energy%20revenues%20and%20to%20target%20in%20particular%20investments%20and%20projects%20which%20are%20aimed%20at%20growing%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20revenue%E2%80%9D.%20Pyatt%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20the%20reason%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20why%20you%20saw%20our%20last%20sanctions%20package%20including%20measures%20specifically%20targeting%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%20in%20Russia.%20Our%20aim%20there%2C%20again%2C%20is%20to%20deny%20Russia%20future%20energy%20revenue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2024%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fassistant-secretary-geoffrey-pyatt-north-american-gas-forum%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Pyatt%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CRussia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20overturned%20the%20international%20energy%20order.%E2%80%9D%20With%20%E2%80%9CRussia%E2%80%99s%20weaponisation%20of%20its%20oil%20and%20gas%20resources%2C%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bit%5D%20is%20never%20going%20to%20be%20viewed%20again%20as%20a%20reliable%20energy%20supplier.%E2%80%9D%20Pyatt%20%C2%A0pointed%20out%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20remarkable%20success%20with%20which%20Europe%20has%20de-risked%20its%20dependency%20on%20Russian%20gas%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20%E2%80%9CAmerican%20producers%20have%20played%20an%20indispensable%20role%20in%20helping%20to%20fulfil%20European%20energy%20security%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPyatt%20further%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CRussia%20which%20until%202022%20was%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20oil%20and%20gas%20exporter%2C%20has%20now%20put%20itself%20more%20or%20less%20permanently%20into%20the%20penalty%20box.%20And%20I%20think%20however%20and%20whenever%20the%20tragedy%20in%20Ukraine%20comes%20to%20an%20end%2C%20the%20market%20is%20never%20again%20going%20to%20look%20at%20Russia%20as%20a%20reliable%20investment%20location%20or%20look%20at%20Russia%20as%20a%20reliable%20supplier.%20So%20that%20means%E2%80%A6there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20continued%20demand%20for%20energy%20that%20the%20United%20States%20produces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20interaction%20with%20James%20O%E2%80%99Brien%20and%20Pyatt%20on%20November%208%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.murphy.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fmurphy-this-is-an-existential-moment-for-ukraine%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CBut%2520the%2520IEA%2520projects%2520Russia%2527s%2Cin%2520oil%2520and%2520gas%2520revenue.%5C%22%3EUS%20Senator%20Chris%20Murphy%3C%2Fa%3E%20spoke%20at%20a%20US%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreign.senate.gov%2Fhearings%2Fus-national-security-interests-in-ukraine%5C%22%3Ehearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20U.S.%20national%20security%20interests%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20IEA%20projects%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20globally%20traded%20oil%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20by%2050%25%20by%202030%2C%20and%20their%20net%20income%20from%20gas%20sales%20is%20going%20to%20fall%20from%20%2475%20billion%20to%20%2430%20billion.%20You%E2%80%99re%20spending%20already%206%25%20of%20your%20GDP%2C%20and%20you%20have%20a%20potentially%20catastrophic%20fall%20coming%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenue.%20That%20is%20one%20of%20the%20things%2C%20maybe%20the%20primary%20factor%20that%20may%20push%20Russia%20to%20the%20table%20to%20try%20to%20drive%20a%20conclusion%20to%20this%20conflict.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fassistant-secretary-geoffrey-pyatt-north-american-gas-forum%2F%5C%22%3EPyatt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstructural%20decline%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenue%20that%20Russia%20is%20confronting%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20working%20as%20hard%20as%20we%20can%20to%20accelerate%20that%20trend.%20We%20do%20that%20through%20two%20mechanisms%3B%20One%20is%20by%20accelerating%20our%20energy%20transition%2C%20both%20here%20in%20the%20United%20States%20but%20also%20globally%2C%20as%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20done%20through%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20to%20reduce%20the%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels.%20%E2%80%A6But%20the%20other%20aspect%20of%20this%20is%20what%20we%20are%20doing%20systematically%20to%20reduce%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20revenue.%20Just%20last%20week%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20we%20levelled%20new%20sanctions%20against%20a%20project%20in%20the%20Arctic%2C%20Arctic%20LNG%202%2C%20which%20is%20Novatech%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20LNG%20project%2C%20which%20Novatech%20set%20in%20motion%20with%20the%20aspiration%20of%20developing%20Russia%20as%20the%20largest%20LNG%20exporter%20in%20the%20world.%20Our%20objective%20is%20to%20kill%20that%20project.%20And%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20that%20through%20our%20sanctions%20working%20with%20our%20partners%20in%20the%20G7%20and%20beyond.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArctic%20LNG%202%20project%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsukraine.rbc.ua%2Fnews%2Fu-s-wants-to-kill-russian-gas-project-arctic-1699476181.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20managed%20by%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Novatek%2C%20focuses%20on%20natural%20gas%20extraction%20and%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20(LNG)%20production.%20On%20November%202%2C%20the%20US%20included%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%20into%20its%20sanctions%20list%2C%20targeting%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20energy%20sector%20production%20and%20export%20capabilities.%20The%20project%20is%20run%20by%20LLC%20Arctic%20LNG%202%2C%20a%20joint%20venture%20with%20PJSC%20NOVATEK%20(60%25)%2C%20TotalEnergies%20consortium%20(10%25)%2C%20Chinese%20corporations%20CNPC%20(10%25)%20and%20CNOOC%20(10%25)%2C%20and%20JAPAN%20ARCTIC%20LNG%20(a%20consortium%20of%20Japanese%20companies%20MITSUI%20and%20JOGMEC)%20(10%25).%20These%20sanctions%20are%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20punitive%20measures%20by%20the%20US%20against%20Russia%2C%20emerging%20from%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENovatek%20has%20been%20actively%20advancing%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%2C%20a%20significant%20initiative%20aimed%20at%20substantially%20increasing%20LNG%20production.%20The%20project%20is%20envisaged%20to%20elevate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20global%20market%20share%20in%20LNG%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%2020%25%2C%20and%20particularly%20it%20stands%20as%20a%20one-of-a-kind%20undertaking%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20the%20first%20completed%20production%20line%20for%20LNG%20on%20a%20gravity-based%20platform%20within%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%2C%20situated%20in%20Murmansk.%20This%20colossal%20platform%2C%20weighing%20over%20600%2C000%20tonnes%2C%20is%20set%20to%20be%20pushed%20along%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20to%20the%20Utrenneye%20field%20on%20the%20Gydan%20Peninsula%20in%20the%20Yamal-Nenets%20Autonomous%20Area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20the%20full%20realisation%20of%20the%20project%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20will%20feature%20three%20liquefaction%20trains%20capable%20of%20producing%20a%20total%20of%2019.8%20million%20tonnes%20per%20annum%20(MTPA)%20of%20LNG%2C%20along%20with%20up%20to%201.6%20MTPA%20of%20stable%20gas%20condensate%20(SGC).%20The%20scale%20and%20uniqueness%20of%20this%20endeavour%20underscore%20its%20significance%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20to%20enhance%20its%20presence%20in%20the%20global%20LNG%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ERussia%20has%20dismissed%20the%20impact%20of%20Western%20sanctions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asserting%20that%20they%20are%20employed%20by%20the%20United%20States%20to%20eliminate%20Moscow%20as%20a%20competitor%20in%20the%20global%20energy%20supplies%20arena.%20These%20sanctions%20do%20not%20directly%20apply%20to%20the%20project%20or%20its%20shareholders.%20However%2C%20concerns%20were%20raised%20about%20potential%20complications%20in%20how%20Mitsui%20and%20JOGMEC%20provide%20support%20for%20the%20project%2C%20possibly%20leading%20to%20delays%20in%20production%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Russian%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20is%20distinguished%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eseveral%20key%20features%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20represents%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20inaugural%20initiative%20for%20the%20serial%20production%20of%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20(LNG)%20lines%20based%20on%20gravity-based%20structures%20(GBS).%20The%20utilisation%20of%20this%20construction%20technology%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20substantial%20localization%20of%20equipment%20and%20material%20production%20in%20Russia%2C%20ensures%20cost-effectiveness%2C%20boosting%20the%20competitiveness%20of%20Russian%20LNG%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Russia%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20also%20adheres%20to%20high%20environmental%20standards%2C%20as%20the%20GBS%20construction%20eliminates%20the%20need%20for%20a%20liquefaction%20plant%20at%20the%20production%20site.%20Instead%2C%20LNG%20lines%20are%20linked%20from%20the%20Murmansk%20region%20to%20the%20Yamal%20field%20along%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20(NSR)%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20environmental%20impact.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20project%20enhances%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20more%20than%2030%25%20reduction%20in%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20per%20tonne%20of%20LNG%20compared%20to%20the%20industry%20average.%20This%20positions%20Russia%20favourably%20amid%20the%20global%20transition%20to%20a%20low-carbon%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20successful%20commissioning%20of%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20is%20anticipated%20to%20significantly%20increase%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20overall%20LNG%20production%2C%20accounting%20for%20over%20half%20of%20the%20load%20of%20the%20NSR%20by%202030%2C%20as%20projected%20by%20the%20Russian%20government.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20project%20contributes%20to%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Russian%20Arctic%20economy%2C%20involving%20numerous%20domestic%20enterprises%20and%20creating%20over%2080%2C000%20jobs%20across%20the%20country.%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20represents%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20third%20LNG%20project%2C%20following%20the%20Sakhalin-2%20project%20launched%20in%20February%202009%20and%20the%20Yamal%20LNG%20project%20initiated%20in%20December%202017.%20Upon%20completion%2C%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20is%20expected%20to%20contribute%20approximately%2019.8%20million%20tonnes%20per%20year%2C%20equivalent%20to%2027%20billion%20cubic%20meters%20of%20gas%20annually%2C%20according%20to%20Konstantin%20Simonov%2C%20the%20director-general%20of%20the%20National%20Energy%20Security%20Fund.%20Russia%20is%20not%20only%20a%20major%20producer%20of%20LNG%20but%20also%20a%20significant%20supplier%20of%20pipeline%20gas%2C%20solidifying%20its%20position%20as%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20energy%20producers%20globally.%20Despite%20facing%20Western%20energy%20embargoes%20in%20response%20to%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20continues%20to%20supply%20more%20gas%20to%20world%20markets%2C%20both%20in%20pipeline%20and%20liquefied%20forms%2C%20according%20to%20Simonov.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20consumers%20of%20LNG%20are%20primarily%20Asian%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20India.%20Spain%20and%20France%20are%20also%20significant%20European%20importers%20of%20Russian%20LNG%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20Russian%20Arctic.%20The%20increased%20capacities%20of%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20are%20expected%20to%20amplify%20the%20volume%20of%20LNG%20deliveries%20to%20these%20countries%2C%20utilising%20the%20Northern%20Sea%20Route%20(NSR)%20as%20a%20strategic%20transit%20route.%20This%20expansion%20aims%20to%20enhance%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20the%20global%20gas%20market%2C%20enabling%20it%20to%20manage%20the%20challenges%20of%20reconfiguring%20gas%20exports%20in%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20sanctions%20have%20presented%20new%20challenges%20for%20Novatek%2C%20the%20operator%20of%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20project%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3Eoutlined%20by%20Simonov%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20primary%20segment%20of%20the%20first%20line%20of%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20was%20produced%20before%20the%20imposition%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20LNG%20industry.%20Novatek%20had%20utilised%20technologies%20from%20the%20German%20company%20Linde%2C%20with%20other%20foreign%20suppliers%2C%20including%20the%20American%20company%20Baker%20Hughes%2C%20also%20contributing%20to%20the%20project.%20However%2C%20post-sanctions%2C%20Baker%20Hughes%20refused%20to%20supply%20the%20full%20number%20of%20turbines%20required%20for%20the%20project.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsputnikglobe.com%2F20230722%2Fsecond-to-none-arctic-lng-2-to-boost-russias-share-in-world-energy-market-1112063345.html%5C%22%3ECritics%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20rather%20than%20hindering%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20industrial%20development%2C%20Western%20sanctions%20would%20serve%20as%20a%20catalyst%20for%20boosting%20domestic%20producers%20and%20technologies%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20actively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fus-working-with-allies-over-sanctions-russian-arctic-lng-project-state-dept-2023-11-08%2F%5C%22%3Ecollaborating%20with%20partner%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20address%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Russian%20LNG%20project%20in%20the%20Arctic.%20The%20Office%20of%20Foreign%20Assets%20Control%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Department%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fofac.treasury.gov%2Frecent-actions%2F20231102%5C%22%3Eissued%20a%20general%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20permits%20the%20wind-down%20of%20transactions%20related%20to%20Arctic%20LNG-2.%20This%20authorisation%20is%20effective%20through%20January%2031%2C%202024.%20The%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20State%20Department%20emphasised%20ongoing%20coordination%20with%20partner%20nations%20as%20the%20January%20deadline%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENovatek%20holds%20a%2060%25%20stake%20in%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20and%20aims%20to%20commence%20production%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20This%20project%20is%20pivotal%20for%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20ambitions%20to%20secure%2020%25%20of%20the%20global%20LNG%20market%20by%202035%2C%20up%20from%20the%20current%208%25.%20The%20new%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG-2%20project%20are%20specifically%20targeted%20at%20degrading%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20future%20energy%20production%20and%20export%20capabilities%2C%20while%20ensuring%20the%20continued%20flow%20of%20energy%20to%20global%20markets%2C%20according%20to%20a%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20US%20State%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20emphasised%20that%20the%20US%20does%20not%20have%20a%20strategic%20interest%20in%20reducing%20the%20global%20supply%20of%20energy%2C%20as%20this%20would%20lead%20to%20increased%20energy%20prices%20worldwide%2C%20benefiting%20Moscow.%20Despite%20the%20sanctions%2C%20the%20US%20maintained%20its%20position%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20LNG%20exporter%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20the%20current%20year%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20Energy%20Information%20Administration.%20The%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%20underscored%20the%20importance%20of%20close%20coordination%20with%20partners%20on%20sanctions%20issues%20and%20affirmed%20the%20continuation%20of%20such%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20energy%20landscape%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20is%20currently%20grappling%20with%20different%20dimensions%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fworld-energy-outlook-2022%2Fexecutive-summary%5C%22%3Eenergy%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20characterised%20by%20unprecedented%20challenges.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20no%20doubt%20transformed%20the%20economic%20recovery%20from%20the%20pandemic%20into%20a%20full-fledged%20energy%20disorder.%20As%20the%20largest%20global%20exporter%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20restrictions%20on%20natural%20gas%20supply%20to%20Europe%2C%20coupled%20with%20European%20sanctions%20on%20Russian%20oil%20and%20coal%20imports%2C%20are%20disrupting%20a%20crucial%20route%20of%20global%20energy%20trade.%20While%20all%20fuels%20are%20impacted%2C%20gas%20markets%20are%20at%20the%20forefront%2C%20with%20Russia%20attempting%20to%20exert%20influence%20by%20subjecting%20countries%20to%20higher%20energy%20costs%20and%20supply%20deficits.%20Spot%20prices%20for%20natural%20gas%20skyrocketed%20to%20unprecedented%20levels.%20The%20soaring%20prices%20of%20gas%20and%20coal%20contributed%20significantly%20to%20a%2090%25%20increase%20in%20electricity%20costs%20worldwide.%20To%20compensate%20for%20the%20shortfall%20in%20Russian%20gas%20supply%2C%20Europe%20sought%20to%20import%20additional%20quantities%20of%20LNG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20players%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20gas%20production%20include%20Gazprom%20and%20Novatek%2C%20while%20several%20oil%20companies%2C%20including%20Rosneft%2C%20also%20contribute%20to%20gas%20production.%20Gazprom%2C%20a%20state-owned%20entity%2C%20remains%20the%20largest%20gas%20producer%2C%20although%20its%20share%20has%20decreased%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20due%20to%20expansions%20by%20Novatek%20and%20Rosneft.%20Nevertheless%2C%20Gazprom%20still%20contributed%20to%2068%25%20of%20Russian%20gas%20production%20in%202021.%20Geographically%2C%20gas%20production%20has%20shifted%20from%20West%20Siberia%20to%20areas%20like%20Yamal%2C%20Eastern%20Siberia%2C%20the%20Far%20East%20and%20offshore%20Arctic%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20extensive%20gas%20export%20pipeline%20network%20includes%20transit%20routes%20through%20Belarus%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20as%20well%20as%20direct%20pipelines%20into%20Europe%20(such%20as%20Nord%20Stream%2C%20Blue%20Stream%20and%20TurkStream).%20The%20completion%20of%20the%20Nord%20Stream%20II%20pipeline%20in%202021%20faced%20challenges%20as%20the%20German%20government%20withheld%20certification%20following%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Russian%20natural%20gas%20accounted%20for%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20European%20Union%20gas%20demand%2C%20representing%2045%25%20of%20imports%20and%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20demand%20in%202021%2C%20with%20Germany%2C%20Turkey%20and%20Italy%20as%20the%20primary%20importers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20initiatives%20include%20the%20Power%20of%20Siberia%20pipeline%2C%20a%20major%20eastward%20gas%20export%20pipeline%20connecting%20far%20east%20fields%20directly%20to%20China.%20With%20a%20capacity%20of%2038%20bcm%2C%20it%20aims%20to%20gradually%20increase%20exports%20to%2038%20bcm%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20Russia%20is%20also%20contemplating%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Power%20of%20Siberia-2%20pipeline%2C%20which%20could%20supply%20China%20from%20West%20Siberian%20gas%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiversification%20efforts%20extend%20to%20LNG%20development%2C%20with%20Russia%20targeting%20110-190%20bcm%2Fyear%20LNG%20exports%20by%202025.%20In%202021%2C%20Russia%20ranked%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth-largest%20LNG%20exporter%2C%20shipping%2040%20bcm%20and%20constituting%20around%208%25%20of%20global%20LNG%20supply.%20Also%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20focus%20on%20the%20Arctic%20aims%20to%20boost%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%2C%20leveraging%20over%2080%25%20of%20natural%20gas%20production%20and%20an%20estimated%2020%25%20of%20crude%20production.%20While%20climate%20change%20poses%20challenges%2C%20it%20also%20opens%20opportunities%20for%20expanded%20access%20to%20Arctic%20trade%20routes%2C%20enhancing%20flexibility%20in%20seaborne%20fossil%20fuel%20deliveries%2C%20especially%20to%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frussiancouncil.ru%2Fen%2Farcticoil%23russia%5C%22%3Eestimates%20from%20both%20the%20Organisation%20of%20the%20Petroleum%20Exporting%20Countries%20(OPEC)%20and%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20(IEA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20global%20energy%20demand%20is%20expected%20to%20increase%20by%2040-60%25%20by%202040%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%20In%20this%20future%20energy%20landscape%2C%20oil%20is%20anticipated%20to%20maintain%20a%20leading%20role%2C%20constituting%2025-27%25%20of%20the%20total%20supply%2C%20while%20gas%20will%20make%20up%2024%E2%80%9326%25%20(compared%20to%20today%E2%80%99s%20figures%20of%2035%25%20and%2026%25%2C%20respectively).%20Notably%2C%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20in%202040%20is%20projected%20to%20occur%20in%20deposits%20that%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20explored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20these%20forecasts%20and%20considering%20the%20potential%20of%20undiscovered%20oil%20and%20gas%20reserves%20in%20the%20Arctic%20Shelf%2C%20estimated%20at%2090%20billion%20barrels%20of%20oil%20and%2047%20trillion%20cubic%20meters%20of%20natural%20gas%2C%20the%20offshore%20resources%20in%20the%20Arctic%20could%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20sustaining%20current%20production%20levels%20and%20fostering%20future%20growth%20in%20the%20medium%20and%20long%20term.%20This%20underscores%20the%20strategic%20importance%20of%20the%20Arctic%20region%20in%20meeting%20global%20energy%20demands%20and%20shaping%20the%20future%20of%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20new%20sanctions%20in%20place%2C%20and%20as%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20ambitious%20energy%20drive%20gets%20underway%2C%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20Russia%20will%20be%20able%20to%20appropriate%20the%20oil%20and%20natural%20gas%20reserves%20in%20the%20Arctic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EK.M%20Seethi%2C%20an%20ICSSR%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20is%20Academic%20Advisor%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficps.mgu.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2F%5C%22%3EInternational%20Centre%20for%20Polar%20Studies%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ICPS)%20and%20Director%2C%20Inter%20University%20Centre%20for%20Social%20Science%20Research%20and%20Extension%20(IUCSSRE)%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20University%2C%20Kerala.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700402014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19192144%2Fbelokameka-LNG-center.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fwhat-do-us-sanctions-on-russias-arctic-lng-2-project-mean-for-the-world-energy-order%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20is%20poised%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20and%20dictate%20the%20terms%20of%20energy%20trade%20in%20the%20coming%20decades.%20The%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Arctic%20LNG%202%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20precursor%20of%20this%20changing%20scenario.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fwhat-do-us-sanctions-on-russias-arctic-lng-2-project-mean-for-the-world-energy-order%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nigeria%20frees%204%2C000%20prisoners%20to%20ease%20jail%20crowding%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700401463000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105334796%2Cimgsize-7974.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnigeria-frees-4000-prisoners-to-ease-jail-crowding%2Farticleshow%2F105334761.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105334761.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThousands%20of%20detainees%20across%20Nigeria%20have%20been%20released%20from%20prison%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20tackle%20overcrowding%2C%20interior%20minister%20Olubunmi%20Tunji-Ojo%20said%20Saturday%20on%20social%20media.%20The%20move%20marks%20part%20of%20a%20drive%20by%20Nigerian%20President%20Bola%