vasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20The%20blockade%20has%20been%20ongoing%20for%20more%20than%2010%20days%2C%20causing%20severe%20difficulties%20for%20the%20affected%20drivers%20who%20are%20facing%20limited%20food%2C%20water%2C%20and%20fuel.%20Ukrainian%20officials%20stated%20that%20an%20agreement%20to%20end%20the%20protest%20has%20not%20been%20reached%20between%20Kyiv%20and%20Warsaw.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20flow%20of%20goods%20across%20the%20border%20has%20significantly%20decreased%2C%20impacting%20Ukraine's%20food%20shipments%20by%20road.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Faround-3000-trucks-stuck-at-ukrainian-border-due-to-polish-drivers-blockade%2Farticleshow%2F105334480.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Faround-3000-trucks-stuck-at-ukrainian-border-due-to-polish-drivers-blockade%2Famp_articleshow%2F105334480.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Faround-3000-trucks-stuck-at-ukrainian-border-due-to-polish-drivers-blockade%2Famp_articleshow%2F105334480.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Heartbreak%20for%20hosts%20India%20as%20Australia%20win%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700400480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-australia-world-cup_6365819.jpg%3F20231119165352%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcricket-world-cup-heartbreak-for-hosts-india-as-australia-win-in-final-13011609%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Australia%20have%20won%20the%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20by%20six%20wickets%20after%20a%20Travis%20Head%20century%20took%20them%20to%20victory%20over%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1200%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fcricket-world-cup-heartbreak-for-hosts-india-as-australia-win-in-final-13011609%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fcricket-world-cup-heartbreak-for-hosts-india-as-australia-win-in-final-13011609%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fcricket-world-cup-heartbreak-for-hosts-india-as-australia-win-in-final-13011609%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chhath%20Puja%3A%20A%20Celebration%20of%20Nature%20and%20Subaltern%20Culture%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19185442%2FChhath_Puja_Ritual_from_India.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EChhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20Hindu%20festival%20that%20is%20dedicated%20to%20the%20worship%20of%20the%20sun%20god%20Surya%20and%20his%20sister%20Chhathi%20Maiya%2C%20who%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20sources%20of%20life%2C%20energy%20and%20healing%20on%20earth.%20It%20is%20an%20ancient%20festival%20that%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20the%20past%2C%20when%20our%20forefathers%20used%20to%20perform%20rituals%20to%20thank%20the%20sun%20for%20sustaining%20life%20on%20earth.%20Chhath%20Puja%20is%20celebrated%20six%20days%20after%20Diwali%2C%20on%20the%20sixth%20day%20of%20the%20lunar%20month%20of%20Kartika%20(October%E2%80%93November)%20in%20the%20Hindu%20calendar%20Vikram%20Samvat.%20It%20is%20also%20called%20Surya%20Shashthi%20Vrat%2C%20with%20the%20word%20chhat%20coming%20from%20shasthi%20or%20the%20sixth%20day%20of%20the%20new%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20celebrates%20the%20bond%20between%20humans%20and%20nature%2C%20and%20the%20power%20of%20faith%20and%20perseverance.%20The%20festival%20involves%20various%20rituals%20over%20four%20days%2C%20such%20as%20holy%20bathing%2C%20fasting%2C%20standing%20in%20water%20and%20offering%20prayers%20and%20water%20to%20the%20setting%20and%20rising%20sun.%20The%20devotees%20also%20prepare%20and%20distribute%20prasad%2C%20a%20religious%20food%2C%20made%20of%20natural%20ingredients%20such%20as%20wheat%20flour%2C%20jaggery%2C%20fruits%20and%20milk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20transcends%20caste%2C%20class%20and%20gender%20barriers%2C%20and%20is%20open%20to%20anyone%20who%20wants%20to%20express%20gratitude%20and%20devotion%20to%20the%20sun%20god%20and%20Chhathi%20Maiya.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20mainly%20observed%20by%20the%20Bahujan%20communities%20of%20Bihar%2C%20who%20have%20preserved%20and%20propagated%20this%20festival%20for%20generations.%20Chhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20reflects%20the%20subaltern%20culture%20and%20identity%20of%20these%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Nahay%20Khay%2C%20the%20first%20day%2C%20the%20devotees%20take%20a%20holy%20bath%20in%20a%20river%20or%20a%20pond%20and%20clean%20their%20houses.%20They%20also%20cook%20food%20without%20salt%2C%20onion%20or%20garlic%20and%20eat%20only%20one%20meal%20in%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20second%20day%2C%20Kharna%2C%20the%20devotees%20observe%20a%20fast%20from%20sunrise%20to%20sunset.%20They%20break%20their%20fast%20in%20the%20evening%20after%20offering%20prayers%20to%20the%20sun%20and%20the%20moon.%20They%20eat%20kheer%20(rice%20pudding)%2C%20puris%20(deep-fried%20bread)%20and%20fruits.%20They%20also%20prepare%20thekua%2C%20a%20sweet%20dish%20made%20of%20wheat%20flour%20and%20jaggery%2C%20which%20is%20the%20main%20prasad%20(offering)%20of%20the%20festival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20third%20day%2C%20Sandhya%20Arghya%2C%20the%20devotees%20observe%20a%20strict%20fast%20without%20water%20or%20food%20for%2036%20hours.%20They%20dress%20up%20in%20new%20or%20clean%20clothes%20and%20offer%20arghya%20(water)%20to%20the%20setting%20sun%20at%20a%20riverbank%20or%20a%20pond.%20They%20also%20light%20earthen%20lamps%20and%20sing%20folk%20songs%20in%20praise%20of%20the%20sun%20god%20and%20Chhathi%20Maiya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20fourth%20day%2C%20Usha%20Arghya%2C%20devotees%20offer%20arghya%20to%20the%20rising%20sun%20at%20the%20same%20place%20where%20they%20offered%20it%20to%20the%20setting%20sun.%20They%20also%20seek%20blessings%20from%20the%20sun%20god%20and%20Chhathi%20Maiya%20for%20the%20well-being%20and%20prosperity%20of%20their%20family%20and%20friends.%20They%20break%20their%20fast%20by%20eating%20the%20prasad%20and%20drinking%20the%20water%20that%20was%20used%20for%20the%20arghya.%20They%20also%20distribute%20the%20prasad%20to%20their%20relatives%20and%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChhath%20Puja%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20eco-friendly%20Hindu%20festivals%2C%20as%20it%20involves%20rituals%20that%20are%20performed%20in%20natural%20settings%2C%20using%20natural%20materials%20and%20respecting%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devotees%20use%20bamboo%20baskets%2C%20earthen%20pots%20and%20clay%20lamps%20for%20the%20rituals%2C%20which%20are%20biodegradable%20and%20do%20not%20cause%20pollution.%20The%20devotees%20prepare%20and%20distribute%20prasad%20made%20of%20natural%20ingredients%20such%20as%20wheat%20flour%2C%20jaggery%2C%20fruits%20and%20milk%2C%20which%20are%20healthy%20and%20nutritious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devotees%20worship%20the%20sun%20god%20and%20Chhathi%20Maiya%2C%20who%20are%20the%20sources%20of%20life%2C%20energy%20and%20healing%20on%20earth.%20They%20thank%20them%20for%20sustaining%20and%20supporting%20life%20on%20earth%20and%20seek%20their%20protection%20and%20blessings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devotees%20perform%20the%20rituals%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20rivers%20or%20other%20water%20bodies%2C%20which%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20sacred%20and%20purifying.%20They%20also%20clean%20the%20surroundings%20and%20avoid%20littering%20or%20polluting%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20showcases%20the%20beauty%20and%20harmony%20of%20nature%20and%20subaltern%20culture.%20It%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20reminds%20us%20of%20our%20dependence%20and%20gratitude%20towards%20the%20sun%2C%20the%20earth%20and%20the%20water%2C%20and%20expresses%20solidarity%20towards%20the%20oppressed%20and%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20festival%20is%20anti-purohit%3B%20it%20does%20not%20involve%20any%20idol%20worship%2C%20temple%20visit%20or%20chanting%20and%20puja%20through%20a%20priest.%20The%20devotees%20perform%20the%20rituals%20themselves%2C%20without%20any%20guidance%20or%20assistance%20from%20a%20priest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20scholars%20have%20suggested%20that%20there%20may%20be%20some%20links%20between%20Chhath%20and%20Buddhism%2C%20as%20both%20religions%20share%20some%20common%20beliefs%20and%20practices.%20For%20example%2C%20both%20Chhath%20and%20Buddhism%20emphasise%20the%20importance%20of%20non-violence%2C%20compassion%20and%20detachment%20from%20worldly%20desires.%20Both%20Chhath%20and%20Buddhism%20also%20involve%20fasting%2C%20meditation%20and%20offering%20prayers%20to%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20scholars%20have%20also%20argued%20that%20Chhath%20may%20have%20been%20influenced%20by%20the%20Buddhist%20king%20Ashoka%2C%20who%20ruled%20over%20the%20region%20where%20Chhath%20originated.%20Ashoka%20was%20a%20patron%20of%20both%20Hinduism%20and%20Buddhism%2C%20and%20he%20promoted%20religious%20harmony%20and%20tolerance%20among%20his%20subjects.%20He%20also%20built%20many%20temples%2C%20stupas%20and%20pillars%20dedicated%20to%20the%20sun%20god%2C%20and%20encouraged%20people%20to%20worship%20the%20sun%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20peace%20and%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20festival%20that%20has%20spread%20to%20different%20parts%20of%20India%20and%20the%20world%20due%20to%20migration%20and%20cultural%20exchange.%20However%2C%20this%20also%20poses%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20authenticity%20and%20originality%20of%20the%20festival%2C%20as%20some%20people%20may%20try%20to%20insert%20religious%20legends%20or%20commercial%20interests%20into%20its%20history%20and%20significance.%20Chhath%20Puja%20is%20a%20festival%20that%20should%20be%20respected%20and%20celebrated%20for%20its%20ecological%20and%20egalitarian%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20festival%20inspires%20us%20to%20live%20a%20simple%20and%20sustainable%20life%2C%20and%20to%20overcome%20the%20challenges%20and%20difficulties%20with%20courage%20and%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Sandeep%20Yadav%20is%20a%20University%20Gold%20Medalist%20in%20PG.%20He%20has%20been%20teaching%20english%20as%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20SLC(E)%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Delhi%20for%20the%20last%2015%20years.%20He%20has%20been%20a%20permanent%20faculty%20member%20at%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Jharkhand%20for%20four%20years.%20He%20has%20published%20many%20books%2C%20including%20%E0%A4%93%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%80%20%E0%A4%94%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A4.%20Yadav%20is%20a%20social%20activist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700400346000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19185442%2FChhath_Puja_Ritual_from_India.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fchhath-puja-a-celebration-of-nature-and-subaltern-culture%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chhath%20Puja%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20eco-friendly%20Hindu%20festivals%2C%20as%20it%20involves%20rituals%20that%20are%20performed%20in%20natural%20settings%2C%20using%20natural%20materials%20and%20respecting%20the%20environment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fchhath-puja-a-celebration-of-nature-and-subaltern-culture%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iran%20rapper%20jailed%20over%20backing%20protests%20freed%20on%20bail%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700399793000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105334423%2Cimgsize-549480.cms%22%2C%22ori